  "text": "From the earliest days, computers have been employed in a variety of areas to help society, including education. The computer was first introduced to the field of education in the 1970s under the aegis of Computer Assisted Instruction (CAI). Efforts at using computers in education were presented by Carbonel in the 1970s. He claimed that a CAI could be endowed with enhanced capabilities by incorporating Artificial Intelligence (AI) techniques to overcome current limitations [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
